{% extends "base.html.jinja" %}

{# Subtitle on one line: linked repo + asof + generation stamp.
   No separate stamp paragraph; no headline sentence repeating the data. #}
{% block subtitle %}
<p class="subtitle">
  for
  {%- if repo_url %} <a href="{{ repo_url }}">{{ report.input.repo }}</a>
  {%- else %} {{ report.input.repo }}
  {%- endif %} ·
  as of {{ prose_asof }} ·
  <span class="stamp">generated {{ generated_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M %Z").strip() }}</span>
</p>
{% endblock %}

{# Drop the long headline sentence — its prefix duplicated the title +
   subtitle, and its numbers (counts past P85/P95) duplicate the
   distribution bar + per-state table. #}
{% block headline %}{% endblock %}

{# Definition moves to the "About this report" footer (collapsed). #}
{% block definition %}{% endblock %}

{# Banner suppressed for Aging — the divergence caveat (when it fires)
   appears in the "About this report" footer with the other caveats. #}
{% block banner %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{% if not report.items %}
<p>No in-flight items as of {{ report.input.asof }}.</p>
{% else %}

{# ── Distribution stacked bar: situation snapshot. The shape — left-
       light / right-heavy — IS the signal. Color-blind safe palette
       (ColorBrewer YlOrRd, monotonic luminance) + inline count/% text
       so the bar reads in grayscale and via screen readers. ── #}
<div class="dist-bar" role="img" aria-label="{{ bar_aria }}">
  {% for band in aging_distribution %}
  {% if band.count > 0 %}
  <div class="seg"
       style="width: {{ (band.share * 100) | round(2) }}%;
              background: {{ band.bg }}; color: {{ band.fg }};"
       title="{{ band.label }}: {{ band.count }} ({{ (band.share * 100) | round(0, 'common') | int }}%)">
    {{ band.count }} · {{ (band.share * 100) | round(0, 'common') | int }}%
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
</div>
<div class="dist-legend">
  {% for band in aging_distribution %}
    <span><span class="swatch" style="background: {{ band.bg }}"></span>{{ band.label }}
      {%- if band.lower is none %} (&lt; {{ "%.1f"|format(band.upper) }}d)
      {%- elif band.upper is none %} (≥ {{ "%.1f"|format(band.lower) }}d)
      {%- else %} ({{ "%.1f"|format(band.lower) }}–{{ "%.1f"|format(band.upper) }}d)
      {%- endif -%}
    </span>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
<p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#666; margin: 0.3rem 0 1rem;">
{{ report.items|length }} in flight
{%- if report.in_flight_total != report.items|length %}
 (excluded {{ report.excluded_above_max_age }} with age > {{ report.input.max_age_days }}d
  from a pool of {{ report.in_flight_total }})
{%- endif -%}
. Thresholds: observed cycle times of {{ report.completed_count }} PRs that
merged {{ report.input.history_start }} → {{ report.input.history_end }}.
</p>

{# ── Interactive chart, named for navigation by heading. ──────────── #}
<h2>WIP Aging</h2>
<div id="aging-chart" style="width:100%; min-height:380px;"></div>
<script>{{ vega_bundle | safe }}</script>
<script>
  vegaEmbed("#aging-chart", {{ vega_spec_json | safe }}, {
    actions: {export: true, source: false, compiled: false, editor: false},
    renderer: "svg"
  }).catch(function(err) {
    document.getElementById("aging-chart").innerText =
      "Interactive chart failed to render: " + err;
  });
</script>

{# ── Next actions: oldest past-P85 per state, rightmost-first. ────── #}
{% if top_interventions %}
<h2>Next actions</h2>
<div>
{% for iv in top_interventions %}
  <div class="intervention">
    <span class="state"><span class="pill">{{ iv.current_state }}</span></span>
    <span class="id">
      {%- if iv.pr_url -%}
        <a href="{{ iv.pr_url }}">{{ iv.item_id }}</a>
      {%- else -%}
        {{ iv.item_id }}
      {%- endif -%}
    </span>
    <span class="age">{{ iv.age_days }}d</span>
    <span class="title">{{ iv.title[:100] }}</span>
  </div>
{% endfor %}
</div>
{% else %}
<h2>Next actions</h2>
<p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:#137333">
✓ No items past P85 — pipeline is on track relative to recent history.
</p>
{% endif %}

{# ── Per-state bottleneck table. ───────────────────────────────────── #}
<h2>Per-state aging</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Stage</th>
      <th class="num">Count</th>
      <th class="num">Age P50</th>
      <th class="num">Oldest</th>
      <th class="num">At risk (P50–P85)</th>
      <th class="num">Past P85</th>
      <th class="num">Past P95</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for row in per_state_diagnostic %}
    <tr>
      <td><span class="pill">{{ row.state }}</span></td>
      <td class="num">{{ row.count }}</td>
      <td class="num">
        {%- if row.median_age_days is none -%}—{%- else -%}{{ row.median_age_days }}d{%- endif -%}
      </td>
      <td class="num">
        {%- if row.oldest_age_days is none -%}—{%- else -%}{{ row.oldest_age_days }}d{%- endif -%}
      </td>
      <td class="num">{{ row.at_risk_p50_to_p85 }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ row.past_p85 }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ row.past_p95 }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#666; max-width:65ch">
<strong>At risk</strong> = items past the 50th-percentile cycle time
but not yet past the 85th. By conditional probability, an item past
P50 has at least double the starting chance of also missing the 85th-
percentile forecast (≥30% versus 15% at age 0). Per Vacanti's
<em>WWIBD</em> recipe, this is the cohort that needs a conversation
NOW — while there's time to swarm, split, or escalate.
</p>

{% endif %}
{% endblock %}

{# Suppress base's auto-rendered sections. #}
{% block key_insight %}{% endblock %}
{% block next_actions %}{% endblock %}
{% block caveats %}{% endblock %}
{% block reproduce %}{% endblock %}
{% block vocabulary %}{% endblock %}

{% block detail %}
{% if past_p85_top %}
<details>
<summary>
  Oldest items past P85
  {%- if past_p85_total > 50 %} (showing 50 of {{ past_p85_total }}){% endif %}
</summary>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>#</th><th class="num">Age</th><th>Stage</th><th>Title</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for it in past_p85_top %}
  <tr>
    <td>
      {%- if it.pr_url -%}
        <a href="{{ it.pr_url }}">{{ it.item_id }}</a>
      {%- else -%}
        {{ it.item_id }}
      {%- endif -%}
    </td>
    <td class="num">{{ it.age_days }}d</td>
    <td><span class="pill">{{ it.current_state }}</span></td>
    <td>{{ it.title[:80] }}</td>
  </tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
</details>
{% endif %}

<details>
<summary>Reproduce this report</summary>
<table>
  <tr><th>Workflow</th><td>
    {% for s in report.input.workflow %}<span class="pill">{{ s }}</span>{% if not loop.last %} {% endif %}{% endfor %}
  </td></tr>
  <tr>
    <th>Percentile training window</th>
    <td>
      {{ report.input.history_start }} → {{ report.input.history_end }}
      ({{ report.completed_count }} completed PRs)
    </td>
  </tr>
  {% if report.input.max_age_days is not none %}
  <tr>
    <th>Max-age filter</th>
    <td>{{ report.input.max_age_days }} days
        ({{ report.excluded_above_max_age }} of {{ report.in_flight_total }} excluded)
    </td>
  </tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>
<div class="invocation">{{ invocation }}</div>
</details>

<details>
<summary>About this report</summary>
<p><strong>What this shows.</strong> {{ definition }}</p>

<h3>How to read the percentile lines</h3>
<p>
The four threshold lines on the chart are <strong>observed cycle
times</strong> of PRs that actually merged in the training window —
exactly the same percentile values as Vacanti's Scatterplot. No
simulation, no Monte Carlo: take the {{ report.completed_count }} PRs that
merged in this window, sort their actual cycle times, pick the values
at rank 50%, 70%, 85%, and 95%.
</p>
<p>
The actionable framing — Vacanti's recipe in <em>When Will It Be
Done?</em> — is to read each line as a conditional-probability
checkpoint. (The math is standard; Vacanti's contribution is applying
it to the Aging chart.) Pick the 85th percentile as your forecast: a
new PR starts with a 15% chance of violating it (by definition of the
85th-percentile rule). When that PR's age crosses the 50th percentile
<em>without</em> finishing, it has self-selected out of the fast half —
its remaining chance of also exceeding the 85th-percentile threshold
has doubled to 30%.
</p>
<p>
The arithmetic, with the population framed as 100 PRs:
</p>
<ul style="font-size:0.95rem; max-width:62ch">
  <li>At <strong>P50</strong>: 50 PRs survived past the 50th. Of those,
      15 historically also went past P85. <strong>30%</strong> chance
      of missing the forecast.</li>
  <li>At <strong>P70</strong>: 30 PRs survived. Of those, 15 missed
      P85. <strong>50%</strong> chance.</li>
  <li>At <strong>P85</strong>: 15 PRs survived. All 15 missed P85 by
      definition. <strong>100%</strong> — the forecast has already
      been violated.</li>
  <li>At <strong>P95</strong>: 5 PRs survived. Deep tail — these are
      decisions about expedite, split, or drop.</li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size:0.95rem;">
The math comes from the survival function of the empirical
distribution:
<code>P(cycle &gt; P85 | cycle &gt; P50) = P(cycle &gt; P85) / P(cycle
&gt; P50) = 0.15 / 0.50 = 0.30</code>. Nothing about it is
forecast-derived or simulated.
</p>

{% if other_caveats %}
<p><strong>Other notes</strong></p>
<ul style="font-size:0.9rem; color:#555">
{% for c in other_caveats %}
  <li>{{ c }}</li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}

<p><strong>Vocabulary</strong></p>
<dl>
{% for term, defn in vocabulary.items() %}
  <dt><strong>{{ term }}</strong></dt>
  <dd>{{ defn }}</dd>
{% endfor %}
</dl>
</details>
{% endblock %}
